cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SY

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) because it deals with link prediction in graphs, which is a common problem in social network analysis. It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Development and Programming), as the paper proposes a new approach for link prediction that relies on higher-order analysis of the graph topology. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper treats the link prediction problem as a supervised classification problem and proposes a set of features that depend on the patterns or motifs that a pair of nodes occurs in. It could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as the paper proposes two optimizations related to constructing the classification dataset from the graph. Finally, it could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control), as link prediction has important applications in several domains such as security, transportation, and recommendation systems.
